before.enText: especially of a problem or a difficult situation

data.enText: to happen; to start to exist

data.chText: 如有任何变化，我们随时通知他们。
data.enText: We keep them informed of any changes as they arise.

data.chText: 必要时孩子应该受到管教。
data.enText: Children should be disciplined when the need arises (= when it is necessary) .
A storm arose during the night.
to happen as a result of a particular situation

data.chText: 道路交通事故造成的伤害
data.enText: injuries arising out of a road accident

data.chText: 身体上的原因可以引起情绪或精神上的问题。
data.enText: Emotional or mental problems can arise from a physical cause.

data.chText: 上次会议记录方面有无尚待解决的事项？
data.enText: Are there any matters arising from the minutes of the last meeting?
to begin to exist or develop

data.chText: 城里出现了好几种新行业。
data.enText: Several new industries arose in the town.
to get out of bed; to stand up
to come together to protest about sth or to fight for sth

data.chText: 农民奋起反对奴役他们的人。
data.enText: The peasants arose against their masters.

before.enText: of a mountain, a tall building, etc.

data.enText: to become visible gradually as you move towards it

simple_means.memory_skill: a 表加强 + rise 出现 → 出现

ex.chText: 一艘军舰出现在港口附近。
ex.enText: A warship appeared near the harbour.

ex.chText: 她曾上过全国性电视节目。

synonyms.bx: 强调进入视野为人所见，也指公开露面为公众所看见。

ex.enText: A crisis has arisen in the Foreign Office.

ex.chText: 太阳从云层后面露出来了。
ex.enText: The sun emerged from behind the clouds.
A submarine emerged from the sea.

ex.chText: 我们探讨得再深入一点就发现，问题开始出现了。
ex.enText: When we look a bit deeper, problems begin to emerge.

synonyms.bx: 指从某个掩蔽处出现或摆脱遮挡物而被看见，强调缓缓出现的过程，常后接介词 from。

ex.chText: 雾中隐隐现出一艘小船。
ex.enText: A boat loomed out of the fog.

ex.chText: 一座岛屿赫然出现在地平线上。
ex.enText: An island loomed on the horizon.

synonyms.bx: 尤指轮廓不清、令人惊恐地隐现。

ex.enText: Her worry showed in her eyes.

ex.chText: 西班牙的经济开始显露出复苏的迹象。
ex.enText: Spain's economy began to show signs of recovery.

synonyms.bx: 语气较强，强调明显地表现出来。

ex.zh: 出现麻烦/分歧/议题/机会/难题/问题

tr: get up and out of bed
example: I get up at 7 A.M. every day
A slight unpleasantness arose from this discussion
The smoke arose from the forest fire
The mist uprose from the meadows
The audience got up and applauded
A new religious movement originated in that country
a love that sprang up from friendship
the idea for the book grew out of a short story

value.def: If a situation or problem arises, it begins to exist or people start to become aware of it.

example.ex: ...if a problem arises later in the pregnancy...
example.tran: 如果在怀孕后期出现问题

example.ex: The birds also attack crops when the opportunity arises.
example.tran: 一有机会鸟儿们也会破坏庄稼。

value.def: If something arises from a particular situation, or arises out of it, it is created or caused by the situation.

example.ex: ...an overwhelming sense of guilt arising from my actions...
example.tran: 我的行为带来的沉重的罪恶感

example.ex: The charges arise out of a long-running fraud enquiry by Merseyside police.
example.tran: 这些指控是默西赛德郡警方对诈骗案进行长期调查后提出的。

value.def: If something such as a new species, organization, or system arises, it begins to exist and develop.

example.ex: Heavy Metal music really arose in the late 60s.
example.tran: 重金属音乐真正形成于60年代后期。

value.def: When you arise, you get out of bed in the morning.

example.ex: He arose at 6:30 a.m. as usual.
example.tran: 同往常一样，他在早上6:30起了床。

value.def: When you arise from a sitting or kneeling position, you stand up.

example.ex: When I arose from the chair, my father and Eleanor's father were in deep conversation...
example.tran: 当我从椅子上站起来时，我父亲和埃莉诺的父亲谈兴正浓。

value.def: You can say that something tall such as a building or mountain arises from the ground around it.

example.ex: ...the flat terrace, from which arises the cubic volume of the house.
example.tran: 上面矗立着立方形房屋的露天平台
